rComments: She's a very very  smart person , but man she cannot teach at all, your exam are the complete opposite of what she's giving in the assignment
She is the worst professor ever. Take fluid with another professor if you have the chance to.
Worst prof everrrrrrr dont everrr take this course or any other courses with her. she is so bad.

She runs the seminars portion of the class, which is very interesting and has great speakers. It is very easy to get all the points for this portion of the class. She only wants a handful of pages written throughout the semester and you get full marks.

Course material is incredibly disorganized: a random collection of videos and documents (not even her own work), 0 example problems. Lectures are nearly impossible to follow as she vaguely describes concepts with no examples. All testing methods are obscure and expectations are far from clear. Lab instructions are non-existant. She cannot teach.
I don't know how she is as a researcher but as a professor; I think she expects a lot for the quality of her teaching.
She explains well, but is very boring. Her exams are tricky and hard. I wouldnt recommend her as a prof !

Even though she's pretty chill, her lectures are very slow and don't cover enough material. Expectations can be quite confusing and she can't explain anything well. Exams are 50/50, very theory based which make it quite challenging. Overall, she's mediocre, but at least she's nice.

You can learn more from COVID-19 since it won't discriminate people. The exam exemption was a deceptive stunt. She has a weird sense of ethics and professionalism. Overall, Mismatching prof. and course. It is amazing how she talks about one thing and does another. BTW, I Wonder which topic of professionalism is related to this incident.

Everyone commenting about the exam exemption are right. Should have been upfront about exempting some people she felt knew the material well enough. Overall the professional practice part of the course was simple, and she had no effect on it for the most part.

Very inspiring course! To be a successful PRO engineer you must find an inner circle. She formed an exclusive club inside the class and promised members A+ without taking a final exam. For secrecy, she asked the members not to spill the beans. If you want special treatments and leverages, learn to obey and memorize names and quotes.

The seminars were interesting and even if they werent mandatory I would still attend but the professor herself is awful. Exempting select students from the final exam with no warning is ridiculous. Pulling a stunt like this with all the stress and anxiety lingering around is disgusting. I hope there is some drastic corrective measure.

The class is good, the seminars are actually interesting. The only thing I did not like was that she sent emails to students of her choice telling them that they were exempt from doing the exam and that they were gonna get 100% because for her they knew everything there was to know and telling them not to tell fellow students. not ethical

Professional Practice. It is a part of the Engineering Lab. Her section is only worth 7%. But if you fail her section you fail the course. She is obsessed with an abstract value of morality and ethics. Do not forget to memorize meaningless quotes. Eg. Why are engineers licensed Because they have a responsibility to the public".

She is really hard woman, I got C about this class, and this is also my first year here, my five assignments are good(85/100),my two projects are good(80/100), I asked five of my classmates in this class, just one past this class, be careful everybody!!

First off, she is an extremely smart professor (used to teach at MIT). With that being said, sometimes she would explain things and they went right over my head. Even when asking her to re-explain certain concepts, she would sometimes seem annoyed that I wasn't able to understand them the first time around. The tests/midterms/finals are tricky.
I don't think she really understands the basic material that she's teaching. She is either incompetent or just uninterested in teaching.
Good, straightforward course. Helpful and fantastically intelligent prof. She expects you to think on your feet for exams, though they are NOT ridiculously challenging.
She's an extremely smart woman and a great professor. Some questions in the exams can be tricky and unexpected and require a lot of thinking. Be prepare and you'll be fine.
love this courseeeeeeee
